By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) – The Nigeria Centre for Disease Control has announced the confirmation of 453 new cases of COVID-19 infections just as it reported that a total of 33,044 patients have been treated and discharged in Nigeria since the index case in February 27, 2020. Disclosing the report via its official twitter handle late Saturday night, the health agency further said that out of the 453 new cases, 75 tested positive in FCT, 71 in Lagos and 53 in Benue state. With the new confirmed cases,  Nigeria has recorded  a total of 46, 140 cases while 942 lives have been lost to the novel Coronavirus pandemic in the country. The report released by the NCDC shows as follows: 453 new cases of #COVID19Nigeria; FCT-75 Lagos-71 Benue-53 Delta-39 Borno-30 Enugu-25 Plateau-24 Osun-20 Abia-19 Oyo-17 Kaduna-16 Kano-13 Ebonyi-13 Ogun-9 Kwara-7 Ondo-6 Gombe-3 Ekiti-2 Akwa Ibom-1 Rivers-1 46,140 confirmed 33,044 discharged 942 deaths While the breakdown of the states is shown below: By Abujah Racheal ABUJA - Nigeria The Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) has announced 643 new COVID-19 cases in the country as total infections from the virus rise to 34,259. The NCDC disclosed this on its official twitter handle on Wednesday. The centre said that 643  new confirmed cases… July 16, 2020 In "Top Stories" By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) -Lagos state on Monday recorded the highest number of infections with 156 cases as the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control confirmed that 595 new persons tested positive. According to the released report, the total confirmed cases in the country is now 33,153 while total… July 14, 2020 In "News" By Abujah Racheal ABUJA - Nigeria has announced 575 new COVID-19 cases in the country as total infections from the virus rise to 33,153. The Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) made this known on its official twitter handle on Monday . The NCDC said that the new confirmed cases as… July 14, 2020 In "Top Stories"